{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> γόνῠ</b>, τό, <br /> <i>genitive</i> γόνατος, <i>Epic dialect</i> and <i>Ionic dialect</i> γούνατος (for γόνϝατος) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 21.591, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.80 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: <i>plural</i> <i>nominative</i> <br /><Level1><b>__A</b></Level1> γούνατα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 5.176, 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Opera et Dies” 587, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.199, “Schwyzer” 694.7 (Chios, 4th c.BC), _genitive_ γουνάτων 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 9.76, _dative_ γούνασι 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 9.455, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.152 (also 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “I.” 2.26), γονάτεσσι 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 16.11, “epigram Gr.” 782 (Halic.)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; also <i>Epic dialect</i> <i>genitive</i> γουνός (explanation as for γόνυος by Hdn.Gr.2.768, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Apollonius Dyscolus Grammaticus “de Syntaxi;” 342.9) 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 11.547: _plural_ γοῦνα 6.511; γούνων 1.407, +others: _dative_ γούνεσσι 9.488, +others (variant{γούνασσι})\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>Aeolic dialect</i> <i>accusative</i> <i>plural</i> γόνα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 7th-6th c.BC: Alcaeus Lyricus 39.7 (probably), but γόννα _accusative_ to 5th c.AD(?): Stephanus Byzantius see entry {Γόννοι}, 12th c.AD: Eustathius Episcopus Thessalonicensis 335.39: _genitive_ _plural_ γόνων 7th-6th c.BC: Alcaeus Lyricus “Supp.” 10: \">Refs 7th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level1><b>__E</b></Level1> has γουνάτων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Hec.” 752, 839, γούνασι “Supp.” 285 (Lyric poetry), “Andr.” 529 (Lyric poetry), but not γουνός (γοῦν᾽\">Refs</a>] <i>accusative</i> <i>plural</i> was read by [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Scholia in “Ph.” 852): _genitive_ _plural_ γεύνων, 5th c.AD(?): Hesychius Legal icographus \">Refs 5th c.AD+</a>]:—<b>knee</b>, γόνυ γουνὸς ἀμείβων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 11.547, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: frequently of <b>clasping the knees</b> in earnest supplication, ἥψατο γούνων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1.512; ἑλεῖν, λαβεῖν γούνων 21.71, 1.407, etc.; τῶν γουνάτων λαβέσθαι 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 9.76 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ποτὶ (variant{περὶ}) or ἀμφὶ γούνασί τινος χεῖρας βαλεῖν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 6.310, 7.142; περὶ γόνυ χέρας ἱκεσίους ἔβαλον 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Orestes” 1414, compare “Ph.” 1622, etc.; τὰ σὰ γούναθ᾽ ἱκάνομαι 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 18.457, compare 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 7.147, etc.; κιχανόμενοι τὰ σὰ γοῦνα ἱκόμεθ᾽ 9.266; ἀντίος ἤλυθε γούνων 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 20.463; γόνυ σὸν ἀμπίσχειν χερί 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Supplices” 165; σοῖς προστίθημι γόνασιν ὠλένας [prev. author] “Andr.” 895 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἐς γούνατά τινι or τινος πεσεῖν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 5.86, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 1607; ἀμφὶ γόνυ τινὸς πίπτειν 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hecuba” 787 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; γόνυ τινός or πρὸς γόνυ προσπίπτειν[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 339, “HF” 79; γόνασί τινος προσπίπτειν [prev. author] “Or.” 1332 (but προσπίτνω σε γόνασιν\">Refs</a>] <b>on my knees</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 485)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; πίπτειν πρὸς τὰ γ. τινος, tini, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 1.19, 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 19.198; also γούνων λίσσεσθαι 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 9.451; ἐλλιτανεύειν 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 10.481; γουνάζεσθαι 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 22.345; ἄντεσθαι πρὸς τῶν γονάτων 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Medea” 710; ἱκετεῦσαι πρὸς τ. γ. 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 58.70. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__E.2</b></Level3> of a sitting posture, φημί μιν ἀσπασίως γ. κάμψειν will be glad to bend <b>the knee</b> so as to sit down and rest, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 7.118, compare 19.72 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; but also, bow <b>the knee</b> in submission, ἐμοὶ κάμψει (<i>intransitive</i>) πᾶν γ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Isa.45.23 \">LXX</a>]; γ. ὀκλάζειν τινί[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"LXX.1Ki.19.18, see entry κάμπτω: ἐπὶ γούνασι\">LXX</a>] <b>on</b> one's <b>knees</b>, ἐπὶ γούνασι πατρός [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 22.500; ποτὶ γ. 5.408; γούνασιν ἐφέσσεσθαι φίλον υἱόν 9.455; σ᾽ ἐπ᾽ ἐμοῖσι.. γούνεσσι καθίσσας 9.488; τόν ῥά οἱ.. ἐπὶ γούνασι θῆκεν 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 19.401; ἐν τοῖς γόνασί τινος στρέφεσθαι 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 617b \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; πέπλον.. θεῖναι Ἀθηναίης ἐπὶ γούνασιν to lay it on her <b>lap</b> (as an offering), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 6.92, compare “Schwyzer” [same place]: hence _metaphorically_, θεῶν ἐν γούνασι κεῖται\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] it rests <b>in the lap of</b>.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 17.514, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 1.267, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; but ἐν γούνασιν πίτνοντα Νίκας victorious, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “I.” 2.26. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__E.3</b></Level3> of the knees as the seat of strength, ἐν δὲ βίην ὤμοισι καὶ ἐν γούνεσσιν ἔθηκε [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 17.569 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; of swiftness, λαιψηρά γ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 22.204, etc.; γούνατά τινος λύειν disable, kill him, 5.176 \">Refs</a>], etc.; ὑπὸ γούνατ᾽ ἔλυσεν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 11.579 \">Refs</a>]; βλάπτειν γ. τινι, κάματος δ᾽ ὑπὸ γ. ἐδάμνα, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 7.271, 21.52 \">Refs</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, αὐτοῦ λύτο γούνατα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 21.114, etc. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__E.4</b></Level3> <i>metaphorically</i>, ἐς γόνυ βάλλειν bring down upon <b>the knee</b>, i. e. humble, conquer, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 6.27 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐς γ. ῥίπτειν, κλίνειν, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Appianus Historicus “Bella Civilia” 3.20, 30; ἐς γ. ἐλθεῖν 6th c.AD: Procopius Caesariensis Historicus “Historia Arcana” 14, “Pers.” 1.17; Ἀσία δὲ χθὼν.. ἐπὶ γόνυ κέκλιται 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 931 (Lyric poetry). \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__E.5</b></Level3> proverbial, ἀπωτέρω ἢ γόνυ κνάμα 'blood is thicker than water', 'charity begins at home', [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 16.18; γ. κνήμης ἔγγιον 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Ethica Nicomachea” 1168b8, 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 9.383b. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__E.II</b></Level2> <b>joint</b> of grasses or plants, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.98, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 4.5.26, 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Historia Plantarum” 8.2.4, 3rd c.AD: Porphyrius Tyrius Philosophus “de Antro Nympharum - Porphyrii Opuscula” 19 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]. (Cf. Sanskrit <i>jā´nu</i>, Latin <i>genu</i>, etc.)","strongNumber":"G1119","accentedUnicode":"γόνυ","shortDef":"knee; \"to bend the knee\" means \"to kneel (in submission or worship)\"","mediumDef":"knee; \"to bend the knee\" means \"to kneel (in submission or worship)\" <br /><b>the knee,</b> <ref='Luk.22.41'>Lk. 22:41</ref>; <ref='Heb.12.12'>Heb. 12:12</ref>, et al.","stepGloss":"a knee","stepTransliteration":"gonu","count":12,"_es_Definition":"rodilla","_zh_tw_Definition":"膝蓋, 脆下","_zh_Definition":"膝盖, 脆下","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"đầu gối","_zh_tw_Gloss":"膝","_es_Gloss":"una rodilla ","_zh_Gloss":"膝"}]}